data-triple-N3.o: "Vertebrates /vrtibrts/ are animals that are members of the subphylum Vertebrata /-/. Vertebrates include the overwhelming majority of the phylum Chordata, with currently about 64,000 species described. Vertebrates include the jawless fish, bony fish, sharks and rays, amphibians, reptiles, mammals, and birds. Extant vertebrates range in size from the frog species Paedophryne amauensis, at as little as 7.7mm (0.3inch), to the blue whale, at up to 33m (110ft)."@en
